est\",\n                \"summary\": \"Retrieve a request\",\n                \"description\": \"Each rider's request goes through the following status changes:\\n\\n| Status               | Description                                                  |\\n| -------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |\\n| `processing`         | Initial state. The request is still being processed, it is not yet clear if the request will be matched or not. |\\n| `noDriversAvailable` | The system has determined that it cannot match the request within the constraints set by the rider. The system will permanently stop looking for drivers for this request. |\\n| `accepted`           | The request has been matched to a driver. The following variables are now available:  `scheduledPickupAddress`, ` scheduledPickupLocation`, ` scheduledPickupTs`, ` scheduledDropoffAddress`, ` scheduledDropoffLocation`, ` scheduledDropoffTs`, ` pickupEta`, ` dropoffEta`, ` vehicleId`, ` driverId`,` pickupWalkingDuration`, ` pickupWalkingPolyline`, ` dropoffWalkingDuration`, ` dropoffWalkingPolyline`, `estimatedPickupTime`, `estimatedDropoffTime` |\\n| `arriving`         | The driver is approaching the pickup point. The exact ETA may vary based on implementation details, but should be around 2 minutes. At this point the rider should be ready to board the vehicle when it arrives. |\\n| `inProgress`         | The driver has reached the pickup point and picked up the rider. The rider is now in the vehicle. |\\n| `cancelled`          | The request was cancelled. To get more information about the cancellation you can fetch the info from `/requests/{id}/cancellation` The request may or may not have been matched before the cancellation. This can be determined by looking at the `statusChanges` array on the request. |\\n| `serviceDisruption`         | The request will enter this state if it was matched, then that match is disrupted (for example by duty cancellation). Our system 